-1.title: Clementine's Day

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

-1.plot: Love is in the air - and it's pointy and sharp! Ginger just wants one dance with Pear for the Valentine's Day dance - so she dupes Cupid into firing arrows at any fruit that stands in her way.

1.title: Welcome To My Fruitmare

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

1.plot: Orange is haunted by dreams of Teddy Juicer - the monster who juices fruit from the inside while they sleep! It's up to Orange to keep everyone on the fruit cart awake, but when his plan fails, he must dive back into dreamland. Can Orange confront his biggest nightmare in time to save his friends?

2.title: Night of the Veggie Zombies

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

2.plot: Orange finds a cure for his giggle-chuckle-itis, but when zombified vegetables try to suck the life out of him and his juicy friends, they learn a mortal lesson: don't underestimate the power of an annoying laugh.

3.title: Marshmalia

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

3.plot: When the U.S.S. Fruiterprise is attacked by alien broccoli, Captain Orange is forced to crash-land on the sickly-sweet planet of Marshmalia. But the Marshmalians are under the tyrannical rule of Big Rock Candy Monster, and it'll take Captain Orange and his enterprising crew to cook up a plan to save the pacifist creme-puffs.

4.title: Follow the Bouncing Orange

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

4.plot: Pear takes advantage of Orange's gullibility and sends him off on a pointless quest, where he falls in with a group of lobotomized tennis balls that 40-Love his jokes and set him up as king! When he decides to join the "yellow oranges" as they volley into the tennis ball machine, Pear faults himself and launches a rescue mission with the rest of the fruit. But will they reach the court before Orange gets served up a sudden death?

5.title: Dr. Strange Plum

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

5.plot: On a dark and stormy night, Orange and his friends attend a dinner party at Professor Plum's creepy mansion. But are they the guests of honor, or the entrée? One by one, the fruit disappear - and reappear on a platter! Can Orange solve the mystery before he gets sliced, diced, and served?

6.title: Captain Blood Orange

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

6.plot: My brothers, in this episode of show, coconut change religion to Christian. BAD! Annoying Orange good Muslim who worship Prophet, peace be with him. Orange continue try make coconut good Muslim, but coconut not want be Muslim so he get kill by man name Dane, who proclaim as god of supermarket world where fruit peoples live!

7.title: Annoying Cutsie

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

7.plot: The Orange thinks he is being replaced when a new orange called "Cutsie" appears.

8.title: Fruit Plane!

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

8.plot: Mr. Juicy Fun is coming to the grocery store to demonstrate his Fruit Obliterator, so Orange and the gang decide to cash in their frequent flier miles and get outta dodge. But when their pilot, Grandpa Lemon, falls asleep at the helm, Orange must take the controls and fly the fruit to safety. Will he stick the emergency landing, or will the fruit end up obliterated after all?

9.title: Fruitvengers

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

9.plot: After swimming in a vat of mysterious goo, the fruit develop superpowers! Now Orange and the Fruit Vengers must save the grocery store from the evil machinations of the juiciest super-villain ever: Grapefruit.

10.title: Founding Fruit

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

10.plot: It's Fruitdependence Day, and Grandpa Lemon shares an educational (and oddly touching) story about the history of Amerifruit: Orange Washington, John Adamsapple, Thomas Jefferpear, and Benjamin Franklemon escape the tyranny of King George the Grapefruit and bravely fight for freedom for all fruits!

11.title: Lords of Fruitbush

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

11.plot: When the fruit get their rinds handed to them by a squad of bad squash, they decide to form their own gang. But they quickly become embroiled in the grocery store underworld, and a free-for-all food fight threatens to ruin the peace of the produce section. Can a juiceless resolution be found? Or will Orange and his home-fruit be forced to settle the score?

12.title: Fruitastic VoyOrange

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

12.plot: Evil cruciferous aliens abduct Nerville and implant a device in his brain that makes laser beams shoot out of his eyes! Now Orange, Pear, and the rest of the fruit cart crew must shrink to microscopic size and embark on a nerve­-wracking trek through Nerville's body to remove the alien implant - all while fighting off a host of miniaturized alien broccoli!

13.title: Bad News Pears

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

13.plot: Orange, Pear, Midget Apple, and Marshmallow are the worst bowlers in the grocery store league, but Orange refuses to fall down without a fight. So Grandpa Lemon - who hit the lanes hard back in his day - spares some time to train Orange. But will his lessons pull Orange and the team out of the gutter? Or have they pinned their hopes to a fruitless endeavor?

14.title: Sir Juice-A-Lot

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

14.plot: When Passion Fruit is captured by a mysterious dark knight, Orange and his crusaders have to get medieval to save her. But can they storm the castle before Passion is pillaged by a putrid princess? And will Orange's hidden crush finally be revealed?

15.title: Escape from the Planet of the Grapes

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

15.plot: On vacation at a Napa Valley vineyard, the fruit make friends with some locals. But when the sweet and juicy grapes beg Orange to rescue them from the harvester, how can he refuse? Especially when taunted by an obnoxious sour grape with an acidic personality. Will the fruit get the smooth finish they hope for? Or will this turn out to be a very bad year?

16.title: Fruit Loose

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

16.plot: Orange and his friends are shocked to learn that dancing has been banned in the produce section. But when a rug-cutting, rabble-rousing strip of bacon shows up, everyone rallies around him to stage a protest. Can the new kid - with some help from his fruity friends - convince the authorities to let them have some good, clean fun? Or will his radical ideas land them all in produce prison?

17.title: The Day the Store Stood Still

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

17.plot: Obsessed with playing World of Modern Mortal Warfruit, Orange doesn't notice that the Sun is still up in the middle of the night! Earth is no longer spinning, and that can mean only one thing: the Earth Hamster has stopped running in his giant exercise wheel. Wait what?! Can Nerville, Orange, and the rest of the bunch journey to the center of the Earth and get things rolling again before Earth boils in its own juices?

18.title: Orange Belt

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

18.plot: Tired of being beat up by Grapefruit, and desperate to win Passion Fruit's approval, Orange learns the ancient art of Carrot-te. But does Orange have the courage to fight for Passion's honor? Can he prove that he's the hero she's dreaming of? Will he finally defeat Grapefruit, and will he do it all for the glory of love?

19.title: Pop Star

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

19.plot: Orange's terrible singing becomes a pop sensation with the wicked beat from a bag of microwave popcorn! But Popcorn gets cold feet when a Hollywood music mogul wants to sign the band to a huge recording deal and send them out on tour. Can they overcome their fears to find fame and fortune? Or will their rising stars fall short?

20.title: When Fruit Ruled the Earth

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

20.plot: In the time of applesaurs and banandons, the cave-Â­-man Nerville falls in love with a prehistoric babe. But when a Cro-Â­-Magnon named Oog steals her away, Orange hatches a plan to help Nerville win back the cave-Â­-woman of his dreams.

21.title: Meet the Oranges

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

21.plot: When Orange's persnickety parents come to visit, he concocts an elaborate lie to convince them he's leading a successful life. But can the other fruit pull off the charade? Or will Orange's parents see through his faÃ§ade?

22.title: Spaghetti West

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

22.plot: In the Old West, Orange and the gang stumble across a town populated entirely by fruit! But the peaceful residents are shakin' in their boots when a villainous band of Pasta-leros rides into town. With no one else to stand up to the spaghetti outlaws, Orange has to pin on the sheriff's badge. Will he still be standing at high noon? Or will the bandits get the drop on him?

23.title: Fast and Fruitious

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

23.plot: Fasten your seatbelts and start your engines for the First Annual Super Market Super Aisle Race! When an injury prevents Midget Apple from driving, Orange suits up to take the wheel. Can he survive the brutal and ruthless world of illegal street racing? Or will his rind get peeled by a bunch of French-Canadian cheeses?

24.title: Boys vs. Girls

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

24.plot: When a little light-hearted teasing between the girls' sleepover and the boys' camp-out escalates into an all out prank war, Passion Fruit and Orange are pitted against one another. Will they be forced to do battle? Or can they rise above the petty feud?

25.title: Orange the Red

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

25.plot: Orange the Red, Pear Forkbeard, and the rest of the Viking-fruit set sail to explore the arctic seas. When they crash into Greens-land, a barren head of iceberg lettuce populated by leprechauns, Orange is granted three wishes. But will he waste those wishes on willy-nilly wants? Or will he wise up and do away with the wisecracks?

26.title: My Name Is Orange

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

26.plot: When Orange is told he has only 24 hours to live, he decides to make amends with all his friends. But can he change his ways and come to peace with himself before heading off to the fruit cart in the sky? Or will his legacy be to leave his friends eternally annoyed?

27.title: C.E.O. - Chief Executive Orange

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

27.plot: Nerville gets into trouble with some loan sharks, so Orange gets an entry-level sales job to help him get out of debt. But who could have predicted Orange's unexpected and meteoric rise up the corporate ladder? And how will he handle his new-found responsibility?

28.title: Trans. Fruit Bots

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

28.plot: Nerville invents an auto-botic cleaning machine, but the deceptive robot fuses with Nerville's body and takes control of his mind! Orange and the crew must roll out and wage battle to destroy the evil force. Can they defeat the robot and transform Nerville back into himself? Or is there more to this bot than meets the eye?

29.title: Generic Holiday Special

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

29.plot: Since holiday specials are so expensive to film, Nerville and the fruit cart gang decide to make an all-Â­-inclusive holiday special they can air all year round! With the comic stylings of the Unknown Banana, and musical guests Li'l Squishy and Lady Pasta, the show is sure to be a hit! Assuming they can keep Orange from being too annoying.

30.title: An Orange Carol

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

30.plot: It's Christmas Eve, and Orange's annoying antics are spoiling everyone's holiday cheer. Will a visit from three ghosts bring Orange the holiday spirit? Or will he end up alone, annoying only himself?

1.title: Little Foodie Cutie

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

1.plot: With a lifetime supply of anything up for grabs, Orange convinces Midget Apple to flaunt his adorableness and enter the Little Foodie Cutie pageant. Who wants to be the next Little Foodie Cutie? Orange convinces Midget Apple he's adorable enough to win the title - and a lifetime supply of whatever he wants! But they'll have to face off against the super-sweet pageant queen Honey Dew Dew.

2.title: Isle of Dr. Fruitenstein

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

2.plot: When Apple wins a fabulous trip to Fruitastic Island, the others join him. But Dr. Fruitenstein has plans for them that are even worse than a time-share pitch.Who could pass up a free trip to Fruitastic Island? Apple brings all the other fruits along for some fun in the sun. But it seems they are walking straight into Dr. Fruitenstein's trap to create unholy fruit hybrids!

3.title: Orange's Run

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

3.plot: It's the year 3057 and life is perfect in the Fruit Dome. Orange works as a Compost Man, seizing runaway fruits who cannot face their fate of being recycled for the greater good. But when Orange discovers a gruesome truth he winds up on the wrong side of the law.

4.title: Marshmallow Wedding

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

4.plot: Volcanoes, death, mayhem - it's a wedding on Marshmalia! Marshmallow is forced into an arranged marriage to the hideous ravenous beast Grumblala, who might just eat all the guests before the ceremony is even over. But Orange has a plan to save the day! Yay!

5.title: Orange James Orange

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

5.plot: It's up to Secret Agent Orange to outwit the evil Dr. Po and his sinister scheme to thaw all the market's frozen foods.Who can possibly stop the maniacal Dr. Po and his diabolical plot to thaw all the market's frozen foods?One fruit has what it takes. Suave, sophisticated and annoying beyond belief - he's Secret Agent Orange. And he's on a mission.

6.title: Avocadotar

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

6.plot: As a human, Nerville feels he's missing out on the fun - so he enlists the aid of the sinister Broccoli Alien Overlord to become one of the fruits.

7.title: Food Carnival

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

7.plot: Nerville builds a carnival for the fruits to enjoy. But a fun day out turns perilous when the rides start to malfunction, trapping Orange and Passion at the top of the dizzying Ferris wheel. Will they escape alive? And if they do, will Grapefruit ever stop making fun of them?

9.title: Everybody Loves Cabbage

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

9.plot: After he gets his wisdom teeth out, Orange can't speak. So how can he warn the others that their beloved pal Cabbage is actually a veggie-killing maniac?

10.title: King Coco

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

10.plot: The other fruits mock Coconut for not having seeds. But after eating a freak meteor turns him into a ravenous 50-foot beast, the fruits don't annoy him anymore. Instead, they attack him with airplanes to stop his rampage.

11.title: The Further Adventures of Sherleek Holmes

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

11.plot: Crikey! Orange and Pear travel to London only to find their luggage has been lost. Thankfully, famous detective Sherleek Holmes is investigating. But before solving the case, Holmes must decide who can be his new sidekick now that Dr. Watercress is gone.

12.title: Fruiturama

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

12.plot: Orange is frozen in a tub of sorbet, leaving the other fruits free to be productive. But he awakes in a distant dystopian future where they live in fear of the robot Gort. These future fruits claim Orange is the chosen annoying one who can free them all!

13.title: Cereal Killer

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

13.plot: When Crispy Cereal is found crunched, it's up to the mismatched police duo of Orange and Pear to solve the crime. But what happens when all signs point to a citrus culprit?

15.title: Orange Julius Caesar

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

15.plot: In the times of the Romaine Emperor, gladiator Orange achieves glory in the arena. But will victory render him even more annoying than ever? All hail emperor Orange! From mere gladiator to almighty ruler of the Romaine Empire, Orange reigns supreme. But will his hubris be his undoing? Or at least really annoy his subjects?

16.title: Orange Say Knock You Out

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

16.plot: Phat beats and delicious rhymes are needed when the rap crew of wrap sandwiches aims to take over Daneboe's. But is Orange up to the task after an on-stage meltdown?

17.title: Hungry Fruit Games

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

17.plot: After a broccoli invasion, the fruit must battle in an arena of death. But Orange is a lover, not a fighter. Can he and Passion escape their cruel fate together?

24.title: Fruitballs

episode of.title: The High Fructose Adventures of Annoying Orange (TV Series 2012–2014)

24.plot: The fruits of Camp Fruit-A-Wanga have had it with losing - this year they'll beat those stuck-up veggies and win the Grocery Relay trophy! Even if it means arming the evil Broccoli Alien Overlord with a tool to ensure their ultimate destruction.

imdb.plot outline: A tv series of the popular youtube series ''Annoying Orange''. Where Orange goes on an adventure with his friends. His weird friend Nerville basically played by a youtuber has a fear of aliens. So Orange and his friends is the one that can stop the adventure.

plot: A tv series of the popular youtube series ''Annoying Orange''. Where Orange goes on an adventure with his friends. His weird friend Nerville basically played by a youtuber has a fear of aliens. So Orange and his friends is the one that can stop the adventure.::Luca Elliot Sanderson
